Registration and authentication provided directly by Bookbot
By registering or authenticating, Users allow Bookbot to identify them and give them access to dedicated services. The Personal Data is collected and stored for registration or identification purposes only. The Data collected are only those necessary for the provision of the service requested by the Users.
Direct registration (Bookbot)
The User registers by filling out the registration form and providing the Personal Data directly to Bookbot.
Personal Data processed: email address.
Tag Management
This type of service helps the Owner to manage the tags or scripts needed on Bookbot in a centralized fashion.
This results in the Users' Data flowing through these services, potentially resulting in the retention of this Data.
